## ⚙️ Step 4: Feature Engineering
Creating time-based features to help ML models understand temporal patterns.


======================================== CELL 11 (code) ========================================
# Create feature-rich dataframe for ML models
df_ml = df_annual.copy()
df_ml['Year_Num']     = np.arange(len(df_ml))          # 0, 1, 2, ...
df_ml['Sales_Lag1']   = df_ml['Sales_Cr'].shift(1)     # Previous year sales
df_ml['Sales_Lag2']   = df_ml['Sales_Cr'].shift(2)     # 2 years ago
df_ml['Rolling_Mean'] = df_ml['Sales_Cr'].rolling(3).mean()  # 3-year avg
df_ml = df_ml.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)

print("✅ Features created:")
print(df_ml[['FY','Sales_Cr','Year_Num','Sales_Lag1','Sales_Lag2','Rolling_Mean']].to_string(index=False))


